org.openimaj.math.geometry.transforms

Class NullModel<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.math.geometry.transforms.NullModel<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, EstimatableModel<T,T>, Model<T,T>

    public class NullModel<T>
extends Object
implements EstimatableModel<T,T>
    A NullModel models a one-to-one mapping of data. For convenience the EstimatableModel interface is implemented, although estimating does absolutely nothing!
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • estimate

        public boolean estimate(List<? extends IndependentPair<T,T>> data)
        Description copied from interface: EstimatableModel
        Estimates the model from the observations in the list of data. The data must contain at least EstimatableModel.numItemsToEstimate() pairs of dependent and independent data. It may contain more, in which case the estimate method may choose to make use of this data for validation, or obtaining a better model by a least squares method for example.
        Specified by:
        estimate in interface EstimatableModel<T,T>
        Parameters:
        data - Data with which to estimate the model
        Returns:
        true if a successful estimate was made, false otherwise
        See Also:
